{"lemma":"تابِعٌ","slug":"تابِعٌ","root":"ت.ب.ع","root_slug":"ت-ب-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ب-ع","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"تابِع","root":"تبع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":15},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3741"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to continue, carry on"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pursue, follow"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to observe, examine"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to search for, seek"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"following, succeeding, subsequent"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"subsidiary, dependent"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"minor, secondary"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"subordinate, under"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"follower, adherent, partisan"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"subject, citizen, national"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"servant"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"factotum"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a word that agrees with another word in grammatical case"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"function"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"appendix, addendum, supplement"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of تَبِعَ (tabiʕa, “to follow”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3741","headword_ar":"تَابِعٌ","root":"tbE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Following; a follower:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaEN","text_ar":"تَبَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEN","text_ar":"تَابِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that follows in the track"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; (Lth, Az;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is at the kinder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"latter, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything; (TA;) but is used alike as sing. and pl.: (S, Msb, K:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEN","text_ar":"تَابِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tub~aEN","text_ar":"تُبَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tub~aAEN","text_ar":"تُبَّاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) [and, applied to rational beings,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEuwna","text_ar":"تَابِعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaEN","text_ar":"تَبَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atobaAEN","text_ar":"اَتْبَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) or this may be used as a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaEN","text_ar":"تَبَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or it is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEN","text_ar":"تَابِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"page_break","n":296},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamN","text_ar":"خَدَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAdimN","text_ar":"خَادِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, Mgh,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalabN","text_ar":"طَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAlibN","text_ar":"طَالِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.; (K;) or, correctly speaking, it is a quasi-pl. n. (Sb, TA.) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuSal~iY tabaEN","text_ar":"المُصَلِّى تَبَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lAimaAmihi","text_ar":"لاِمَامِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The person praying is a follower of his Imám"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsu tabaEN lahu","text_ar":"النَّاسُ تَبَعٌ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people are followers of him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And it is said in the Kur [xiv. 24, and xl. 50], ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~aA kun~aA lakumo tabaEFA","text_ar":"اـِنَّا كُنَّا لَكُمْ تَبَعًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily we were followers of you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) in which the last word may be a quasi-pl. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEN","text_ar":"تَابِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or it may be an inf. n., meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awiY tabaEK","text_ar":"ذَوِى تَبَعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaEN","text_ar":"تَبَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied as an epithet to the legs of a beast: (Lth, T:) and is also used as [an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant,] signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"legs of a beast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A jinnee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genie, that accompanies a woman and follows her whithersoever she goes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loving her:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEapN","text_ar":"تَابِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a jinneeyeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female genie, that does the same to a man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is added in the latter to give intensiveness to the signification, or to denote evilness of nature, or to convey the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAhiyapN","text_ar":"دَاهِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.: the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tawaAbiEu","text_ar":"تَوَابِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and this means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female associates."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A servant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiyEN","text_ar":"تَبِيعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awi Alt~aAbiEiyna","text_ar":"اَوِ التَّابِعِينَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayori A^uwliY AlA_irobapi","text_ar":"غَيْرِ اُولِى الاـِرْبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxiv. 31], accord. to Th, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Or the servants"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the husband,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as the old man who is perishing by reason of age, and the aged woman."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiyEN","text_ar":"تَبِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One next in the order of time after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaAbap","text_ar":"صَحَابَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; like ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEiY~N","text_ar":"تَابِعِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b6-  And in grammar,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An appositive."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEu Aln~ajomi","text_ar":"تَابِعُ النَّجْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The follower of the asterism;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Pleiades;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a name of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~abaraAn","text_ar":"الدَّبَرَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Hyades;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the five chief stars thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the brightest star among them, a of Taurus"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: this name being given to it as ominous of good; (K;) or as ominous of evil: (O:) or so called because it follows the Pleiades: (T:) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aAbiEu","text_ar":"التَّابِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dbr","text_ar":"دبر"},{"kind":"text","text":", Sh, IB, and others,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuwayobiEN","text_ar":"تُوَيْبِعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which is the dim., (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~uwayobiEu","text_ar":"التُّوَيْبِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dbr","text_ar":"دبر"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tub~aEN","text_ar":"تُبَّعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~ub~aEu","text_ar":"التُّبَّعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], (Aboo-Sa'eed Ed-Dareer, T,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~abaEu","text_ar":"التَّبَعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IB, Z,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aAliY","text_ar":"التَّالِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaAdiY","text_ar":"الحَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IB,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAdY Aln~ujuwmi","text_ar":"حادى النُّجُومِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jdH","text_ar":"جدح"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAdY","text_ar":"حادى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ajomi","text_ar":"النَّجْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Kzw and others.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmijodaHu","text_ar":"المِجْدَحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEiY~N","text_ar":"تَابِعِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEN","text_ar":"تَابِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["TA","S","Msb","K","Kr","Mgh","Lth","T","O","IB","Z"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%B9/","headword_ar":"تابع","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23032#6e9e03","body_html":"<span>التابع: هو كل ثانٍ بإعراب سابقه من جهة واحدة. وخرج بهذا القيد خبر المبتدأ، والمفعول الثاني، والمفعول الثالث، من باب: علمت وأعلمت؛ فإن العامل في هذه الأشياء لا يعمل من جهةٍ واحدة، وهو خمسة أضرب: تأكيد، وصفة، وبدل، وعطف بيان، وعطفٌ بحرف.</span>"}]}}